2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to visualize the inference of a CNN, which is a common research area in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with optimization of a deep CNN and proposes a method to predict relevant image pixels using another network. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly mention robotics, but the topic of monocular depth estimation is relevant to robotics applications such as autonomous navigation. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely sub-category as the paper does not focus on evolutionary algorithms, but rather on the visualization and optimization of CNNs for depth estimation.
